VBadruka School of music and dance and Guruwar Mandal, Hyderabad jointly organised a flute recital of Pandit Venkatesh Godkhindi.Pt. Venkatesh is a retired station director of All India Radio, Dharwad and well-known flautist and vocalist. His performance on the flute takes us back to the traditional style of flute playing. He innovated the instrument to his liking and developed additional blower holes for better impact, especially the Meend effect. He began his concert with RaagMarwaset toteen tal. The next raagSaraswatiwas set toRudra Tal(eleven beats), inVilambit Ghatandteen talindrutand this was the highlight of the concert. He followed it with the popular evening raagYamanagain set toteen tal.He then performed aThumri dhunand concluded his concert with raagBhairavi.He was accompanied on the tabla by local young artiste Samrat Kakkeri. He did his best to follow the senior artiste and showed good promise.On the whole it was a pleasant flute recital of the evening.C. SURESH KUMARBottom Template Starts
